useEffect-Hook
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The useEffect hook in React is used to run code (side effects) when dependencies change, when the component renders, or when the component mounts (loads).

Here are some common use cases for useEffect:

- Fetching data from an API
- Setting up timers
- Listening to browser events
- Updating the document title
- Manually interacting with the DOM
- Subscribing to and unsubscribing from services
